column2: Bright- clear- level approximately 4" below normal.
Bright- clear- level below normal- slight ripples.
Level up 7" in 5 days- heavy rain for 3 days before reading.
Rain on and off- level down 3" in last week but 4" above normal.
5+" of rain in last two weeks.  Lake level: very high
Ice out 3/24/87 (very early). Dry- warm winter 17' of ice in test spot on 2/2/87. Dry spring.
Slight ripple- floating green stuff- about 1.5 ft. rain last week- lots of weeds starting to grow.
Medium ripple on water- more weeds- and the green slime is increasing.
Green slime is lessening- water color changing to brown- and about 1" of rain in last 2 weeks.
Rained 0.8" on 7/4/1987.  The green slime is almost gone.
Color changing to brown.  It rained about 3.5 inches in last 2 weeks.
Lake like pea soup- fishing has been off all year- last test of the year.  Water level: up est. 6"
Ice out 4/8- little rain this year- water warmer than usual.
Lake rising- weeds showing above water.
Weeds fully up- black slime in shadows- very little rain.
4.5" rain over last 10 days- lake about normal.
Lake has clear up over past few days- not normal but good.
Ice out 4/18- water temp. near shore at 2 ft. under is 42 F.
Bright sun- light chop- weeds starting to show.
Bright. Sun- light chop- 1.75 in. rain past week- deepest reading since 6/24/87.
Light chop- 2.5 in. rain last 2 days- level was dropping last week- now is normal.
Calm- ice off 3/4- 1st pair loons 4/6- lots of migrating ducks.
Big boats stirring up lake every weekend- weeds starting- level going down.  Water level: up 3"
Weeds thick- hard to find a swimming spot.
Weeds bad- fishing picking up a little.
Weeds not through surface as in past weeks- little rain for 2 weeks.
Heavy winds on 8/24- heavy rain- fishing average- temps in 90's.
Cold at night (58 F)- nice day- weeds going down- fishing slow.
A lot of rain last week- fishing slow- weeds down.
Cold- water up 6 inches from last week.
Cold at night- water temp. is 60 degrees.
Rain for the last two days- lake is up.
Water is cold for swimming- Northerns are hitting.
Cold as usual.  Fish biting- 7lb northern- pan fish fair.
Rain for good old labor day- 42 degrees- water temp is 46 degrees.
No swimming- cold rain- fishing is slow.
Not a good spring for lake people- fishing is slow.
Twenty-one weekends of rain in a row.  Lake is back to normal- weeds are high.
Last 2 weeks in June- bass-northern were good-sunfish also.
Good rain in the last two weeks- the lake is up a little- weeds are normal.
Lake and water high- cold spring.
No secchi depth on the field sheet- took the number given on the lab sheet.
The best reading in 3 years.  Hope this keeps up.
Boats back in full swing.  Will be coming down on readings now- but hoping to stay at 6' or so.
We had 5-6" rain.  Lake up about 1'.
Water level up from last week due to rainfall.
85 degrees in the shade.  Hot- slow fishing.
90 degree weather- lots of boats- water skiing- algae up- lost 2' on reading in one week.
High water level from latest rain fall.
High water- a lot of rain.
Bass and northern hitting ( ).  High water.
Lowered our dock.  Water went down 2' in one week- bass biting.
Rain on the 4th. Not a good sample.
Coming back on readings.  Looking a lot better.
No rain for almost a month-Northerns hitting.
Bottom temp. 59 F- bottom D.O. 0 mg/l.
Bottom temp. 59 F- bottom D.O. 0 mg/l.
Bottom temp. 56 F- bottom D.O. 0 mg/l.
Bottom temp. 64 F- bottom D.O. 1.5 mg/l.
Clear sunny morning.Beautiful day Temps in the 70's. Light wind slight ripple on the lake. I was assisted my fellow property owner Mike Salwasser
Satellite Day Path 26 clear day no clouds  86 degrees F Assisted by fellow property owner Mike Salwasser. Wind from the south west at 10 mph
Sunny with high hazy whispering clouds.
Satellite Day - took water clarity reading
